    {
      "id": "d6fb61ce185be5f5db77973bc8cd5fe0bc56b1c3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 931,
        "name": "Timothy Day",
        "email": "timday@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "timday"
      },
      "date": "2024-02-22 02:25:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI think this may be related to https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17451 (bug when using lctl dl with a large number of OBD devices). I applied this patch and tested the command. The error goes away - but the devices beyond 166 don't show up in the list.\n\nDo you have any thoughts about how I could debug this?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "0494e64c2fbc1ad49f82bb66164d35dd880cf143",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2024-02-22 02:32:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nOh I didn't know about that ticket but yes its the same issue. This allows the library to handle the extra data but the kernel code needs to be updated as well.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b7f7d58d87323741b6f25d84637461108c9ccdb4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2024-02-22 10:36:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified+1\n\nPassed enforced test review-ldiskfs-dne-arm on RHEL 8.8/aarch64, RHEL 8.8/x86_64 uploaded by Onyx Autotest 2 from onyx-91vm7: https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/979d0c1d-2dac-4816-b305-bc6fc462eaf1 ran 5 tests.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "6d300cb47515ce00f225e91934bc441f26e00b71",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 148,
        "name": "Chris Horn",
        "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
        "username": "hornc"
      },
      "date": "2024-02-22 17:16:42.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nTest case?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "840a6bc06b5b87ab68b2e2cea3549e436ea3664b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2024-02-22 17:25:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe test cases will be in the next few patches on top of this. We need a patch for lctl dl which I believe sanity 55b will test since it makes many devices. I need to complete the lctl get_param *.*.stats as well as a normal user. Lastly we need to support many routers which is the ticket for this.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "2b5f3337e10578ec9a5b02fe6c26b88f1134b776",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 931,
        "name": "Timothy Day",
        "email": "timday@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "timday"
      },
      "date": "2024-02-22 17:34:47.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> The test cases will be in the next few patches on top of this. We need a patch for lctl dl which I believe sanity 55b will test since it makes many devices. I need to complete the lctl get_param *.*.stats as well as a normal user. Lastly we need to support many routers which is the ticket for this.\n\nYou're right about sanity/55a and sanity/55b. Both read from a sysfs file right now. It should be converted to use 'lctl dl' after the fix.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "2fc6525f45c75b4e374178826103b8e142f57f5b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 148,
        "name": "Chris Horn",
        "email": "chris.horn@hpe.com",
        "username": "hornc"
      },
      "date": "2024-02-22 18:02:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> The test cases will be in the next few patches on top of this. We need a patch for lctl dl which I believe sanity 55b will test since it makes many devices. I need to complete the lctl get_param *.*.stats as well as a normal user. Lastly we need to support many routers which is the ticket for this.\n\nCouldn't you  make a simple sanity-lnet test case for it? e.g. create thousands of peers and import/export ?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
